1 Results 






	Antimicrobial Dressings

































	All you need, all in one.

The critical elements of I.V. site care in an integrated, easy-to-use product.

Request a product evaluation at your facility.



























	Proven to reduce CRBSI and vascular catheter colonization.

Request Clinical Evidence






 





















          
	The difference is clear.

      





Tegaderm™ CHG I.V. Securement Dressing is the only transparent dressing cleared and proven to reduce CRBSI and vascular catheter colonization that aligns with evidence-based guidelines and practice standards. The dressing provides four essential elements you need to protect I.V. sites in one integrated, easy-to-use product.
 

Infection reduction
Site visibility
Consistent application
Catheter securement

How does it work?
Tegaderm™ CHG I.V. Securement Dressings deliver immediate and continuous CHG protection for up to 7 days,* plus all the benefits of our Tegaderm™ I.V. Advanced Securement Dressing. The CHG gel pad is designed to conform around the catheter and hub, and the gel pad remains transparent even in the presence of blood, saline and exudate, providing visibility to the insertion site.
Learn more about Tegaderm™ CHG Dressings in our Tegaderm™ CHG dressings brochure.
Find full specifications, application and removal videos, and Instructions for Use on our product detail page.
*In vitro studies show the dressing is a microbial barrier and protects the insertion site against a variety of gram-positive and gram-negative bacteria and yeast, including organisms most commonly associated with catheter-related bloodstream infections (CRBSI).











          
	Tegaderm™ CHG Dressings for your application.

      

        Check out product detail pages for ordering information and product use guides.
















3M™ Tegaderm™ CHG Chlorhexidine Gluconate I.V. Port Dressing 1665


















3M™ Tegaderm™ CHG Chlorhexidine Gluconate I.V. Securement Dressing


















3M™ PICC / CVC Securement Device + Tegaderm™ CHG Dressing




 



































	How Tegaderm™ CHG Dressings measure up.


Tegaderm™ CHG Dressings are as effective as, or better than, BioPatch® Disks plus adhesive cover dressings at reducing skin flora and preventing regrowth.1,2  Tegaderm™ CHG Dressings also maintain significantly lower counts of skin flora than BioPatch® Disks after seven days on healthy adult subjects.1,2

Get all the details in a Competitive Comparison.

















          
	The all-in-one product that meets standards and guidelines.

      










Tegaderm™ CHG Dressings:

Allow constant site monitoring
Deliver CHG to the skin immediately, regardless of the amount of skin moisture*
Integrate securement features and CHG impregnated gel pads
Include features designed to provide consistant I.V. site protection

Find out how Tegaderm™ CHG Dressings meet the latest Infusion Therapy Standards of Practice. Download 3M’s quick guides to 2016 Infusion Therapy Standards of Practice.
 
Learn about 2016 Infusion Therapy Standards of Practice.
In this two-part webinar, Lisa Gorski, chair of both the 2011 and 2016 INS Standards of Practice Committee, reviews in depth two of the new section topics: Infusion Therapy Practice and Vascular Access Device Management.
 
Watch now.
Part 1: Introduction to the 2016 Infusion Therapy Standards of Practice
Part 2: Infusion Therapy Standards of Practice: Vascular Access Device Management













          
	Watch a video to learn more about what sets Tegaderm™ CHG Dressings apart.

      








 









          
	Evidence, tools and support for a value analysis.

      















